io.undertow.channels

Class GatedStreamSinkChannel

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.undertow.channels.GatedStreamSinkChannel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, Channel, GatheringByteChannel, InterruptibleChannel, WritableByteChannel, org.xnio.channels.CloseableChannel, org.xnio.channels.Configurable, org.xnio.channels.StreamSinkChannel, org.xnio.channels.SuspendableWriteChannel

    public final class GatedStreamSinkChannel
extends Object
implements org.xnio.channels.StreamSinkChannel
    A 'gated' stream sink channel.

    This channel has a gate which starts of closed. When the gate is closed writes will return 0. When the gate is opened writes will resume as normal.

    Author:
    David M. Lloyd

      • openGate

        public void openGate()
              throws IOException
        Open the gate and allow data to flow. Once opened, the gate cannot be closed other than closing the channel.

        If the shutdownWrites() or close() method has already been called this will result it in being invoked on the delegate.

        Throws:
        IOException
